OL,3,CPolice Commissioner Sir Mark Rowley
OL,4,Ccalls for wide reforms and smaller
OL,5,Cforces
OL,7,F"If you've got an overly bureaucratic,
OL,8,Fcomplicated, convoluted sort of
OL,9,Fspaghetti system, all of that
OL,10,Fcomplexity sucks resources away from
OL,11,Fthe locals."
OL,13,F"We're never going to get the money
OL,14,Fthat we would ideally need. The way we
OL,15,Fcan succeed for the public is going to
OL,16,Fcome through big investment in
OL,17,Ftechnology and technology-led reform.
OL,19,F"It's difficult, it won't be a
OL,20,Fstraightforward path, but it is
OL,21,Foverdue."
